<subSubSection id="BEC36531FFF4FFFB6CEEFBDA42F73149" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F66636BAFFF4FFFB6CEEFBDA42F73149" blockId="32.[151,1436,884,1152]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="C4ADEAA8FFF4FFFB6CEEFBDA47103101" bold="true" box="[199,322,1053,1079]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male antennae without spines in antennomeres V or VI; lateral tubercles of the prothorax acute, coincident or not with posterolateral angles; pro- and mesoventral processes less than one-fourth width of the procoxal cavity; elytra without centrobasal crest or carinae. Number of species currently included: 78.
</paragraph>
